+# Initial QuadGK breakpoints. f₀ support is ≪ the integration box, so seeding interior
+# points cuts adaptive over-refinement of the near-zero tails.
+# Inner (para) integrand is smooth → a fixed static seed. Outer (perp) integrand
+# carries Bessel Jₙ(a·v): oscillation frequency ∝ a=k⊥/Ω, so its seed scales with a (built
+# once per call, so a runtime range is fine).
+const _NSEG_IN = 6
+@inline _segs(lo, hi, ::Val{N}) where {N} = ntuple(i -> lo + (hi - lo) * ((i - 1) / N), Val(N + 1))
+@inline _osegs(lo, hi, a) = range(lo, hi, length = max(4, ceil(Int, abs(a) * (hi - lo) / 2)) + 1)
